column5: I was reading the regs and just wanted to be sure before we drive 2.5hrs, that it is open. It says "Bighead River - St. Vincent Twp. (Grey County)." and that is under the extended fall season in zone 16.  I think that means its open near Georgian Bay in Meaford.  Normally it gives you 2 streets where its open between or closed between those 2 streets.  here's the link  http://www.mnr.gov.on.ca/stdprodconsume/groups/lr/@mnr/@letsfish/documents/document/mnr_e001335.pdf  Thanks guys!   Lovetofish
looks like until Dec 31. I used to fish it way up from town many years ago in late fall, may still be that way. Check it may be open all year Hwy 26 to the lake. Check carefully things change.
No it means all of St Vincent township. Quite a lot of fall river open but a lot is private
Check here too: FMZ 14 detailed map so you know when you are in FMZ 14 vs FMZ 16
